The paper discusses a novel two-factor authentication solution that uses a camera to capture images of physical objects chosen by the user. This involves computer vision techniques for image processing and classification, which suggests that the paper could belong to the computer security (cs.CR), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), multimedia (cs.MM), or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. However, given the focus on authentication and security, cs.CR is the most likely sub-category. The use of computer vision techniques for feature extraction and classification also makes cs.CV a likely sub-category. The focus on user experience and usability suggests that cs.HC is also a possible sub-category. The use of machine learning classifiers suggests that cs.LG is another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of images and multimedia techniques suggests that cs.MM is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
